<p><b>Problem2</b>: A gulab jamun, contains sugar syrup up to about 30% of its volume. Find approximately how much syrup would be found in 45 gulab jamuns, each shaped like a cylinder with two hemispherical ends with length 5 cm and diameter 2.8 cm.</p>

<p><br />
<br />
</p>

<p><b>Given</b>: GulabjamunSugerSyrupVolume.Percentage = 30 %</p>

<p>Gulabjamun.Number = 45 Nos.</p>

<p>HemisphericalEnd.DiameterCm = 2.8 Cm </p>

<p>Gulabjamun.LengthCm = 5 Cm</p>

<p><br />
<br />
</p>

<p><b>To Find</b>: GulabjamunSugerSyrupFor45Gulabjamun.VolumeCuCm = ? </p>

<p><br />
<br />
</p>

<p>HemisphericalEnd.RadiusCm = (HemisphericalEnd.DiameterCm/2) Cm</p>

